"filename": "other-exhibitions-and-events.json",
"fields": {
  "title": "Exhibitions, auctions, seminars, presentations",
  "size": "width:675px; height:900px;margin:0 112px;",
  "img": "images/Kalligrafie_Kaiserslautern.jpg",
  "img_alt": "Exhibition visitors Kaiserslautern 2006",
  "unterschrift": "Exhibition visitors at Kimoto exhibition, Kaiserslautern 2006",
  "img_placeholder": "data:image/jpeg;base64,",
  "intro_text": "Kimoto's works have also been on show on a variety of other occasions at solo and group exhibitions since 1972. Moreover Kimoto took part in public art donations auctions regularly, has taught calligraphy lessons and is occasionally seen in public tea ceremonies and Rakusho demonstrations. For an overview see the following list.",
  "body_text": "Exhibitions:\n\n2014 Town hall gallery Riegelsberg\n\n2010/11 \"Power and Powerlessness\", Town Hall Neunkirchen\n\n2010 espace mediArt, Luxembourg · \"Memorial Mark\", Kreissparkasse Kaiserslautern\n\n2009 \"30 Strokes - either way\", calligraphy exhibition adult education center Kaiserslautern · \"Cross/Section\", Saar-Palatinate Park Bexbach\n\n2008 \"Three Views\", \"Art and Migration\", Ramesch, Saarbrücken \n\n2007 Retrospective, Old Castle, Dillingen · Rood mediArt, Luxembourg\n\n2006 Gallery Technical University Kaiserslautern\n\n2005 Robert Schuman House, Catholic Academy Trier\n\n2003 Gallery Simoncini, Luxembourg\n\n2002 Town Hall gallery Saarwellingen\n\n2000 Town Hall gallery Völklingen\n\n1999 Gallery in the Old Brewery, St. Ingbert\n\n1998 Old Castle, Dillingen\n\n1997 Gallery Simoncini, Luxembourg · Gallery 48, Saarbrücken\n\n1996 Gallery Im Hof, St. Wendel\n\n1995 Museum St. Wendel (Mia-Münster House) · Wohnkunst gallery, Karlsruhe · Gallery Im Hof, St. Wendel · VSE electric utility Saarbrücken\n\n1994 Gallery Simoncini, Luxembourg · Gallery 48, Saarbrücken · Bosen Mill, Bosen\n\n1991 Saarland Artists' House, Saarbrücken\n\n1988 Gallery Im Bürgerhaus, Neunkirchen\n\n1987 District administration Wetzlar · Saarland Artists' House, Saarbrücken\n\n1985: Gallery Am Graben, Fulda · Hohaus Museum, Lauterbach · Castle gallery, Bonn · Kunstwerkstatt, Würzburg\n\n1984 Rose gallery, Bielefeld · Art gallery, Luxembourg\n\n1983 Town Hall Neunkirchen\n\n1982: Gallery Spektrum, Frankfurt\n\n1981/82 Protestant Academy, Bad Boll\n\n1981: Gallery Vanille, Emmerich\n\n1980 Gallery Im Zwinger, St. Wendel · Art house Blank, Marburg · Asia house, Frankfurt\n\n1977: Art house Blank, Marburg\n\n1976 Auslandsgesellschaft Intercultural academy, Dortmund · Asia house, Saarbrücken · Gallery Faber, Fulda\n\n1975 Art association Gütersloh\n\n1974: Kunstkontor Blank, Marburg\n\n1973: Gallery Studio 68, Speyer\n\n1972: Gallery Elitzer, Saarbrücken · Gallery Schneider-Sato, Karlsruhe",
  "body2_text": "\n\nArt campaigns:\n\n2011 \"Words in Flow\", event for the campaign \"Art helps Japan\" for the Fukushima victims\n\n2010 \"Cities for Life - Cities against the Death Penalty\"\n\n1994 \"Artists from Saarland for UNICEF\" · Art auctions for the Saarland section of German AIDS Healthcare association (yearly in November) and Amnesty International\n\n1992 \"Action Art\" (Saarland State Diet)\n\n1989 \"Paintings for Africa\", International artists campaign\n\n1987 Touring exhibition \"Artists against Apartheid\"\n\n1984 Touring exhibition \"Orwell 1984\"\n\n1982 \"War and Peace\" (Kassel and Bremen) · \"Allemagne 82/Autour de l’eclectisme\" (Atelier quatre, Sens) · \"Artists against War\" (Kassel and Saarbrücken) · \"Campaign artists catalog\" (Modern gallery in the Saarland museum)\n\n1980 Ink paintings for Terre des Hommes\n\n\n\nCalligraphy and Ink paintings:",
  "size3": "width:787px;height:787px;margin:0 56px;",
  "img3": "../images/Kalligrafie_Kurse.jpg",
  "img3_alt": "Calligraphy Seiji Kimoto",
  "img3_placeholder": "data:image/jpeg;base64,",
  "unterschrift3": "Calligraphy",
  "body3_text": "For several years now Seiji Kimoto has been giving monthly lessons in calligraphy and ink painting to a small group of students. These include practical exercises for brush positioning and brush movement, explanations of the principles of ink painting, and free painting with brush and ink using techniques of Zen painting. Registrations to his seminars are possible. He also hosts workshops on the basics of calligraphy occasionally as side event of his exhibitions, most recently in 2013 at espace mediArt gallery Luxembourg.\n\n\n\nRakusho - Sounding characters:",
  "size4": "width:900px;height:584px;",
  "img4": "../images/Rakusho.jpg",
  "img4_alt": "Rakusho demonstration with Seiji Kimoto",
  "img4_placeholder": "data:image/jpeg;base64,",
  "unterschrift4": "Rakusho demonstration",
  "body4_text": "Along with percussionist and bassist Rudolf P. Schaaf, Seiji Kimoto has participated in a number of improvisational musical-calligraphic stage performances since 2010, partly as a standalone program, partly as supporting program of his exhibitions.\n\n2014 Theater U, Saarbrücken\n\n2014 \"Culture at Saarbrücken-Folsterhöhe\"\n\n2013 \"Raku Sho - The Five Elements\", \"Summer Music Saarbrücken\" at Theater im Viertel (TiV), Saarbrücken Summer Festival\n\n2012 \"Rakusho - Sounding Characters\", supporting programm exhibition \"Power and Powerlessness\", St. John's Church, Saarbrücken\n\n2012 \"Rakusho\", supporting programm Kimoto exhibition, espace mediArt, Luxembourg\n\n2010 \"Rakusho\", supporting programm Kimoto exhibition, espace mediArt, Luxembourg\n\n\n\n",
  "size5": "width:900px; height:598px;",
  "img5": "images/Teezeremonie.jpg",
  "img5_alt": "Tea ceremony with Seiji Kimoto at the Japanese garden Kaiserslautern",
  "unterschrift5": " at the Japanese garden Kaiserslautern",
  "srcLink5": "http://chanoyu.eu/index.php?id=3",
  "lnkText5": "Tea ceremony",
  "img5_placeholder": "data:image/jpeg;base64,",
  "body5_text": "Occasionally Seiji Kimoto is also appearing at public tea ceremony demonstrations, partly in the context of the Japanese Garden's event program in the city of Kaiserslautern, partly as companion event of his exhibitions, most recently in the programme for his exhibition at St. John's Church Saarbrücken in 2012."
}

